The paper discusses object segmentation in computer vision, which is a common topic in the computer vision subfield (cs.CV). The use of Markov random fields and conditional random fields is also a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the comparison of different image labeling methods, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL) or multimedia (cs.MM) subfields.
